<div id="review_2471083248" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2471083248" />
    <a title="Lani" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/19238250-lani"><img alt="Lani" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2471083248?book_show_action=true">Jul 26, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lani" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lani" href="/user/show/19238250-lani">Lani</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2471083248" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer485625095298247087">Tami is from Iran, and has dreamed of freedoms all her life. She gets to come to the US on a travel Visa, but must get married in 90 days if she wants to remain. Can she find someone to marry? Will she find someone she can live with, or will she find true happiness?<br/><br/>I loved this book. It&apos;s unlike anything I&apos;ve ever read. It opened my eyes to what things are like in Iran and helped me to be grateful for the freedoms we have. It started out a bit slow, but I was intrigued from the beginning. I high</span>
  <span id="freeText485625095298247087" style="display:none">Tami is from Iran, and has dreamed of freedoms all her life. She gets to come to the US on a travel Visa, but must get married in 90 days if she wants to remain. Can she find someone to marry? Will she find someone she can live with, or will she find true happiness?<br /><br />I loved this book. It's unlike anything I've ever read. It opened my eyes to what things are like in Iran and helped me to be grateful for the freedoms we have. It started out a bit slow, but I was intrigued from the beginning. I highly recommend it!<br /><br />I received a free copy of this book via Booksprout and am voluntarily leaving a review.</span>
  <a data-text-id="485625095298247087" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

